<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Teches on My Workbook</title><link>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/tech/</link><description>Recent content in Teches on My Workbook</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 02:05:00 +0530</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/tech/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Docker Cleanup</title><link>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/docker-cleanup.html</link><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 02:05:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/docker-cleanup.html</guid><description>&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker stop &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;docker ps -aq&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker rm &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;docker ps -aq&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker rmi -f &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;docker images -aq&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker volume rm &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;docker volume ls -q&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker network prune -f
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker builder prune -a -f
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;docker system prune -a --volumes -f
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>Mount an SMB Share on Linux with systemd Automount</title><link>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/linux-smb-share-automount.html</link><pubDate>Sun, 07 Jun 2026 15:30:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/linux-smb-share-automount.html</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="mount-an-smb-share-on-linux-with-systemd-automount"&gt;Mount an SMB Share on Linux with systemd Automount&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This guide explains how to mount an SMB share on Linux in a standard, clean way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The example uses a persistent mount at:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-text" data-lang="text"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;/mnt/mybox
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;It also uses systemd automount, so the share does not block your system during boot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-is-smb"&gt;What Is SMB?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SMB means &lt;strong&gt;Server Message Block&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is a network file-sharing protocol. In simple words, SMB lets one computer expose a folder over a network so another computer can use that folder almost like a local folder.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Create a Minecraft Left-Click Toggle on Linux Mint Cinnamon</title><link>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/minecraft-left-click-toggle-linux-mint.html</link><pubDate>Sat, 06 Jun 2026 03:05:09 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/minecraft-left-click-toggle-linux-mint.html</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="create-a-minecraft-left-click-toggle-on-linux-mint-cinnamon"&gt;Create a Minecraft Left-Click Toggle on Linux Mint Cinnamon&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This tutorial shows how to make one keyboard key hold left click for Minecraft.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After setup:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Press &lt;code&gt;F8&lt;/code&gt; once to start holding left click.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Press &lt;code&gt;F8&lt;/code&gt; again to stop holding left click.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use this only in single-player or on servers where automation is allowed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-you-need"&gt;What You Need&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This guide is for Linux Mint Cinnamon using X11.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You also need a small tool called &lt;code&gt;xdotool&lt;/code&gt;. It lets Linux press or release mouse buttons from a command.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Permanently Fix Bluetooth Mouse Speed on Linux Mint Cinnamon</title><link>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/fix-mouse-speed-linux-mint.html</link><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 04:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/fix-mouse-speed-linux-mint.html</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;If your Bluetooth mouse speed resets after every restart on Linux Mint Cinnamon, the problem is usually that &lt;code&gt;xinput&lt;/code&gt; changes are temporary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Commands such as &lt;code&gt;xinput set-prop&lt;/code&gt; only affect the current X11 session. After a restart, logout, or Bluetooth reconnect, those settings can reset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The permanent fix is to configure the mouse in two places:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cinnamon&amp;rsquo;s persistent mouse settings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Xorg/libinput device configuration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This guide is for Linux Mint Cinnamon running on X11.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Configure Codex CLI with LM Studio as the Default Local Model Provider</title><link>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/codex-cli-lm-studio-setup.html</link><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 04:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/codex-cli-lm-studio-setup.html</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This guide shows how to configure Codex CLI so it uses LM Studio by default.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="prerequisites"&gt;Prerequisites&lt;/h2&gt;
