&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;#34;id&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;qwen/qwen3-8b&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;#34;object&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;model&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;#34;owned_by&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;ashish&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; ],
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;#34;object&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;list&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="required-files"&gt;Required Files&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This setup needs two Codex config files:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Build Spring Boot JAR Without Local Java Using Docker</title><link>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/build-spring-boot-jar-with-docker-no-java.html</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Jun 2025 10:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/build-spring-boot-jar-with-docker-no-java.html</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;If you’re working on a Spring Boot project that targets Java 17, 21, or 24, but your system only has Java 8 (or no Java at all), building the .jar with mvn clean install becomes impossible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="the-problem-we-want-to"&gt;The Problem: We want to&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the Spring Boot .jar using Docker (no local Java or Maven)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extract only the built .jar to our host system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean up the container, image, and temporary Dockerfile&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Avoid polluting the final image with source code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="the-solution-a-simple-bash-script"&gt;The Solution: A Simple Bash Script&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here’s a script that does everything for you:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>AI Engineering Transition Path</title><link>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/ai-engineering-transition-path.html</link><pubDate>Thu, 15 May 2025 09:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/ai-engineering-transition-path.html</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOTE : This content is presented exactly as it appears in InterviewReady&amp;rsquo;s AI Engineering Transition Path on &lt;a href="https://github.com/InterviewReady/ai-engineering-resources"&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt;. All credit goes to the original authors.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
